        "layoutData": {
          "title": "Setting Goals That Actually Work",
          "paragraphs": [
            "The SMART framework transforms vague wishes into achievable financial goals. Each element makes your goal more actionable: in {{STATE_NAME}}",
            "\"Save $500 for a new laptop\" is better than \"save money.\" Know exactly what you want. in {{STATE_NAME}}",
            "Track your progress with numbers: \"Put $50/month into savings\" lets you see results. in {{STATE_NAME}}",
            "Set realistic targets based on your actual income and expenses. Challenge yourself, but be practical. in {{STATE_NAME}}",
            "Your goal should connect to what matters to you personally and align with your values. in {{STATE_NAME}}",
            "Set a deadline: \"Save $500 by December\" creates urgency and accountability. in {{STATE_NAME}}"
